com.imkrisna.samsung.nservice

Class NSConnection

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.imkrisna.samsung.nservice.NSConnection

  • public class NSConnection
extends Object

    This class is the main process for com.imkrisna.samsung.nservice library for android. NSConnection maintain the discovery, connection, and communication protocol with N-Service capable devices. Since the N-Service connection should be only one instance in an android application, This class instance should be implemented in a Singleton pattern or inside the android Application context.

    NSConnection class instance will notify all registered NSListener instance when any N-Service events occurred such as device discovery found, connected/disconnected events, and messaging events. NSListener instance need to implements abstract/unimplemented methods and registering itself to the NSConnection instance to be able to receive notification from NSConnection.

    Version:
    1.0.1
    Author:
    I Made Krisna Widhiastra (im.krisna@gmail.com)

        public NSConnection(String applicationId, Context context)

        Constructor for NSConnection class. Since the N-Service connection should be only one instance in an android application, This class instance should be implemented in a Singleton pattern or inside the android Application context. 

         NSConnection connection = new NSConnection("1234567890", getApplicationContext());
 NSConnection connection = new NSConnection("NServiceTest", getApplicationContext());
        Parameters:
        applicationId - - Smart Application Project Name (development) or Samsung Seller Apps ID (operating)
        context - - android Context. Suggested to use application context when using single instance pattern

        1.0.0

    • Method Detail

      • searchDevices

        public void searchDevices()

        public void searchDevices()

        Commanding the NSConnection instance to perform UPnP SSDP device search for N-Service capable devices. This method require NSDiscovery class and org.cybergarage.upnp library.

        The search process will be asynchronous and when the N-Serivce capable device found, NSConnection will notify all NSListener on the onDeviceChanged method.

        Since:
        1.0.0

      • startPoller

        public void startPoller()

        public void startPoller()

        This method will initiate connection polling with paired NSDevice. Connection polling will maintain connectivity between android and N-Service device so then the connection will kept alive.

        This method should not be called by external instance to prevent current connection crashed. If it is needed to be called by external instance, the NSConnection instance must be not connected to any device and the poller process already finished.

        Since:
        1.0.0

      • stopPoller

        public void stopPoller()

        public void stopPoller()

        This method is used to stop current connection poller. Stopping connection poller will causing message from N-Service devices cannot be retrieved by NSConnection and after several seconds, the N-Service device will close the connection with android device. Closed connection will causing any messaging from and to N-Service device will failed.

        This method should not be called by external instance, consider using disconnect method to close the connection cleanly. The disconnect method also will stop the connection poller automatically.

        Since:
        1.0.0
